recordings.rmk: Recording lightly filtered.

Female was perched about 8 m above me, calling. Male arrived and sang at 0:52 and 1:08. She flushed at 1:08 to catch an insect, then returned. Striped Rocket Frog (Allobates talamancae) sang several times (e.g., 0:07). Some rain noise. Recording was normalized to -3 dB.
Unusual soft grunting call from up a tree from within dense foliage, out of view. Calls similar to those in XC166666 and XC126182 (but much quieter). Background noise was rain.

A male Slaty-tailed Trogon flew in, perched high in a tree, and began singing. He was joined by one, then two others in singing, but I did not see the others. His song lasted more than 10 minutes after I cut this recording (due to XC size restrictions). There was some airplane noise in the background.
